The pMSSM [57] is obtained from the more general MSSM by making assumptions based on experimental results:
No new source of CP violation beyond the Standard Model. New sources of CP violation are constrained by experimental limits on the electron and neutron electric dipole moments.
No flavour-changing neutral currents. This is implemented by requiring that the matrices for the sfermion masses and trilinear couplings are diagonal.
First- and second-generation universality. The soft-SUSY-breaking mass parameters and the trilinear couplings for the first and second generation are assumed to be the same based on experimental data from, e.g., the neutral kaon system [71].With the above assumptions, and with the choice of a neutralino as the LSP, the pMSSM adds 19 free parameters on top of those of the SM. The complete set of pMSSM parameters is shown in Table 2.Table 2
Description of the 19 additional parameters of the pMSSM model with a neutralino LSP

Parameter
Description

